title: It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia
fullTitle: It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia (TV Series 2005â€“ )

episodes.title: Mac Fights Gay Marriage
episodes.plot: Mac pulls out the big guns to protect the sanctity of marriage, while the rest of the gang reap the rewards of marital bliss.

episodes.title: Dennis Gets Divorced
episodes.plot: Marital bliss turns to marital business, as the gang experiences the emotional and economic tribulations of divorce.

episodes.title: The Gang Buys a Boat
episodes.plot: The gang attempts to open themselves up to the adventures of the sea after they purchase their new boat.

episodes.title: Mac's Big Break
episodes.plot: After Mac wins a radio contest to score a goal on the Flyers' ice, he and Charlie train for the event - badly, while Dennis and Dee start their own radio program.

episodes.title: Mac and Charlie: White Trash
episodes.plot: Mac & Charlie attempt to fix up their old pool after getting rejected by a country club, Dennis, Dee, and Frank attempt to gain entry to the club.

episodes.title: Mac's Mom Burns Her House Down
episodes.plot: Charlie and Mac set up a truly odd couple after Mac's Mom burns the house down, while Frank discovers the importance of paternal care when Dee falls ill.

episodes.title: Who Got Dee Pregnant?
episodes.plot: The gang gets a real 'scare' after Dee reveals she's pregnant, forcing the guys to recall their last hazy Halloween Party to determine if one of them might be the father.

episodes.title: The Gang Gets a New Member
episodes.plot: A blast from the past prompts the guys to expand membership, and Dee to re-consider her future.

episodes.title: Dee Reynolds: Shaping America's Youth
episodes.plot: Motivated by the drama teacher who inspired her, Dee takes a job as a substitute teacher and exposes her students to the culture of Paddy's with a field trip to see the Gang's take on the Lethal Weapon series: Lethal Weapon 5.

episodes.title: Charlie Kelly: King of the Rats
episodes.plot: When keeping the basement rodent-free drives Charlie to the brink, the gang decides to put the cynicism aside and throw a surprise party to cheer him up.

episodes.title: The Gang Gets Stranded in the Woods
episodes.plot: Things go awry as the Gang travels to Atlantic City for a charity benefit. While Frank, Dee and Mac try to survive in the woods, Dennis and Charlie hitch a ride to the city and have the night of their lives.

episodes.title: Dee Gives Birth
episodes.plot: Before Dee's baby arrives, The Gang tries to figure out who is the father by throwing a house party for all her former flings.

episodes.title: A Very Sunny Christmas
episodes.plot: Dennis and Dee decide to teach Frank a lesson "A Christmas Carol"-style, and Mac and Charlie learn some shocking things about their childhood Christmas traditions.
